init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The story is told from the perspective of a young man named Jack, who is a member of a family of scavengers.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Jack and his family are forced to live in a fallout shelter that they have converted into a home.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Jack's father, who is the leader of the family, has taught Jack that the world outside is dangerous and that the only way to survive is to

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: scavenge what they need from the ruins of the old world.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He wants to know what happened to the world and why the United States was the only country to emerge from isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Jack has learned how to use the library's computers to search for information, and he has been able to learn a great deal about the world.
